# Line-ending discipline for the repo.
# Source / config / docs / data → LF (Unix-style) regardless of host OS.
# Windows-only shell scripts keep CRLF so cmd.exe / PowerShell parse them.
#
# Rationale: this is a Next.js / TypeScript project routinely opened from
# both Windows and macOS / Linux worktrees (see also gruntdom-3d-viewer and
# gruntdom-docs-adr siblings). Without this file, Windows checkouts pick up
# core.autocrlf=true and rewrite every file to CRLF on checkout, producing
# noisy diffs against the LF-stored blobs and tripping `diff -rq` between
# worktrees. With `* text=auto eol=lf`, every text file is normalised to LF
# on commit and checked out as LF on every OS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows shell scripts intentionally keep CRLF — required by cmd.exe /
# PowerShell parsers; running them with LF endings causes "command not
# recognized" failures on Windows.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
